##CPGE_SCRIPT
##ScriptVersion: 1.0
##Written: 2026-05-10
##Scene: SCENE_GAMEPLAY
##Author: LordAries1972
##Description: Main gameplay scene — positions player, arms live collision detection, manages FX.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ensure clean slate on entry
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
STOP EFFECTS

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Camera — positioned slightly above and behind player spawn
# POSITION x y z yaw pitch
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
POSITION 0.0 4.0 -8.0 0.0 -10.0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Fade in cleanly from black
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Execute FadeToBlack(0.0, 0.0)
Execute FadeToImage(1.5, 0.0)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Player spawn position
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PLAY_POSITION 0.0 0.0 0.0
WAIT(1.0)
GET_READY

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Set gameplay player state active (PlayerState::ACTIVE = 1)
# SetPlayerState(playerID, stateID)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Execute SetPlayerState(0, 1)
Execute StartPlayerTimer(0)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Collision monitoring
# Player 0 vs wall pixel map (uses GamePlayer collision bitmap)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
DETECT_COLLISION PLAYER 0 WALL 0 ALERT Error "Player hit boundary wall"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Player vs player collision (multiplayer)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
DETECT_COLLISION PLAYER 0 PLAYER 1 32.0 ALERT General "Player-to-player contact"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Audio
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Execute StartPlaybackThread()
Execute SetGlobalVolume(1.0)

ALERT General "Gameplay scene ready."
